# How did Andrei Medvedev manage to cross the Norwegian border and seek asylum?

## Summary
Andrei Medvedev, a former commander with the Russian mercenary Wagner Group, managed to cross the Norwegian border and seek asylum by evading a border patrol with dogs and running through a forest and over thin and breaking ice <font color=#FF3399>[3]</font>. He was arrested shortly after 2am last Friday and taken into custody by Norwegian border guards <font color=#FF3399>[1]</font>. He had fled in fear for his life after refusing to renew his service with Wagner, which he had joined after serving time in prison <font color=#FF3399>[4, 5]</font>. Medvedev had been helped to leave Russia by Gulagu.net, a human rights advocacy group, after he approached them in fear for his life <font color=#FF3399>[5]</font>.

